# 🚀 Loan Default Prediction Dashboard

## 🌐 Live Demo
👉  https://loan-default-prediction-dashboard
6e2q3sqxlier9trnzmj4hd.streamlit.app/ 

## 📊 Overview
This project focuses on predicting whether a loan applicant is likely to default using basic Machine Learning techniques.
The goal is to analyze financial data and extract meaningful insights that help in identifying high-risk applicants. A simple dashboard is also included to visualize key patterns in the dataset.

## 🎯 Objectives
* Understand real-world financial datasets
* Perform data cleaning and preprocessing
* Build a basic machine learning model
* Visualize important insights using graphs
* Create a simple dashboard for analysis

## 🛠️ Tech Stack
* 🐍 Python
* 📊 Pandas
* 🔢 NumPy
* 📉 Matplotlib / Seaborn
* 🤖 Machine Learning (Basic Models)
* 🌐 Streamlit (Dashboard)

## 📈 Key Features
✔ Data preprocessing and cleaning
✔ Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
✔ Basic machine learning model for prediction
✔ Visualization of patterns and trends
✔ Simple interactive dashboard


## 🚀 How to Run the Project
### 🔹 1. Clone the repository
```bash
git clone https://github.com/karunaprathamshetti/loan-default-prediction-dashboard.git
cd loan-default-prediction-dashboard
```
### 🔹 2. Install dependencies
```bash
pip install pandas numpy matplotlib seaborn scikit-learn streamlit
```
### 🔹 3. Run Jupyter Notebook
```bash
jupyter notebook
```
### 🔹 4. Run Dashboard (optional)
```bash
streamlit run dashboard.py
```
          
## 🎯 Results
* Built a basic model to predict loan default risk
* Gained understanding of real-world data handling
* Learned how to transform raw data into insights

